title: xAPI resources
---

![knowledge vs experience](/images/knowledge-vs-experience.jpg 'knowledge vs. experience')

Prior to my recent [visit to the Thingstitute](http://craigwiggins.github.io/2015/04/20/the-thingstitute/), [Dr Brenda Bannan](http://cehd.gmu.edu/people/faculty/bbannan/) asked me to provide a list of [Experience API (xAPI)](http://xapi.adlnet.gov) resources that the participants could use. I pretty quickly with responded with a really long list - not because I'm a fast typist, but because I spend a lot of time at work answering questions about xAPI.

Anyway, I'll soon get around to putting up a proper xAPI wiki/FAQ at adlnet.gov. Until then, enjoy this hailstorm of links - I'll be back later with some updates.

####the basics
* [Background](http://www.adlnet.gov/tla/experience-api/background-and-history.html)
* [Best video that I've found that explains xAPI](https://youtu.be/y42MSS1DJqc)
[![Experience API (aka Tin Can API) Demystified](http://img.youtube.com/vi/y42MSS1DJqc/0.jpg)](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=y42MSS1DJqc)
* [Probably the best xAPI-in-context explanation I've yet seen](http://floatlearning.com/xapicartoon/)

####the confusion
* ["Project Tin Can has concluded. Its successor is the Experience API (xAPI)"](http://www.adlnet.gov/tla/tin-can.html)
* ["We Call it 'Tin Can'"](http://tincanapi.com/2012/12/11/we-call-it-tin-can/)
* [Tin Can Changing Names...Again?](http://www.learndash.com/tin-can-api-changing-names-again/)
* ["There is only one specification: xAPI"](http://elearninfo247.com/2015/01/12/xapi-lrs-the-interview/)

